The paper deals with generating natural language descriptions for videos, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a new neural network architecture that integrates multiple fully convolutional neural networks (FCNs) and Multiple Instance Learning (MIL), which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses a sequence-to-sequence recurrent neural network to generate sentence descriptions, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
